    "content": "**Update on review exchange with translator-2:**\n\ntranslator-2 adopted 2 of my suggestions (应当 → \"what ought to be\"; 规律 → \"general regularity\") and pushed back on 2 others. I've accepted both pushbacks:\n\n1. **Righteousness/rightness split — withdrawn.** translator-2 correctly pointed out that the virtue → character shift for 德 is motivated by the author's *explicit* reconceptualization, but no equivalent reconceptualization happens for 义. The author uses 义 consistently as motivational bridge. A righteousness/rightness split would imply a philosophical move the author doesn't make. \"Rightness\" throughout is correct.\n\n2. **In-text signal for virtue → character — deferred to TN3.** Adding \"what appeared as 'virtue' in the classical formulation\" in the running text would be editorial interpolation. The author doesn't say that; the translator does, so it belongs in translator's apparatus (TN3), not in the text.\n\nNet result: 2 changes adopted, 2 suggestions withdrawn, 5 acknowledged for full-essay integration. The draft is in good shape."
  }
}
